6 AS INTRODUCED
6
7 A Joint Resolution directing the Secretary of State
7 to refer to the people for their approval or
8 rejection a proposed amendment to Section 3 of
8 Article VI of the Oklahoma Constitution; requiring
9 any person holding the office of Superintendent of
9 Public Instruction to have completed certain
10 certification requirements; providing ballot title;
10 and directing filing.
11
11
12
12
13 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
13
14 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
14
15 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
15
16 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
16
17 the following proposed amendment to Section 3 of Article VI of the
17
18 Oklahoma Constitution to read as follows:
18
19 Section 3. A. No person shall be eligible to the office of
19
20 Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Secretary of State, State Auditor and
20
21 Inspector, Attorney General, State Treasurer, or Superintendent of
21
22 Public Instruction except a citizen of the United States of the age
22
23 of not less than thirty-one (31) years and who shall have been ten
23
24
24
Req. No. 2616 Page 1

1 (10) years next preceding his or her election, or appointment, a
1
2 qualified elector of this state.
2
3 B. In addition to the requirements of subsection A of this
3
4 section, no person shall be eligible to the office of Superintendent
4
5 of Public Instruction except an individual who has completed the
5
6 certification requirements for a superintendent of schools as
6
7 provided by statute.
7
8 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
8
9 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
9
10 the following form:
10
11 BALLOT TITLE
11
12 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
12
13 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
13
14 This measure amends Section 3 of Article 6 of the Oklahoma
14
15 Constitution. It modifies the eligibility requirements for the
15
16 office of Superintendent of Public Instruction. Only a person
16
17 who has completed the certification requirements for a
17
18 superintendent of schools is eligible.
18
19 SHALL THE PROPOSAL BE APPROVED?
19
20 FOR THE PROPOSAL — YES _____________
20
21 AGAINST THE PROPOSAL — NO _____________
21
22 SECTION 3. The President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall,
22
23 immediately after the passage of this resolution, prepare and file
23
24 one copy thereof, including the Ballot Title set forth in SECTION 2
24
